Hey @Sean!
@liamgold is right - we'll be improving things related to your use case with that Refresh by adding more APIs for content querying.
Here are some example improvements that should be coming with that Refresh
- Query for web page items without needing to specify a website channel - Query for content items by specifying multiple content types - Query for content items without specifying any content type - Query for content items by their reusable field schema - Query for content items without including the "content type" fields (the custom fields)
@liamgold's approach is basically the same thing we do here [on the Community Portal](https://github.com/Kentico/community-portal/blob/v28.2.1.0/src/Kentico.Community.Portal.Web/Features/SEO/Sitemap.cs)
And you can see what that code generates by [looking at the sitemap.xml](https://community.kentico.com/sitemap.xml).
